criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Male (80%) or Female (20%);

          2. Age 18-55;

          3. Meet the Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders version 5 (DSM-5)
             criteria for Schizophrenia (SZ) or schizoaffective disorder and cannabis use disorder
             with physiological dependence;

          4. Full scale intelligence quotient (IQ) ≥ 80 determined through the Wechsler Test of
             Adult Reading (WTAR);

          5. Daily cigarette smoker ≥ 5 cigarettes per day

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. DSM-5 diagnoses of alcohol, substance or polyuse substance use disorder in the past 6
             months (other than cannabis/caffeine or nicotine);

          2. Currently active suicidal ideation or self-harm (suicidal or non-suicidal) as assessed
             by the Structured Clinical Interview for DSM-5 (SCID-5);

          3. Head injury resulting in loss of consciousness (>5 minutes) and hospitalization;

          4. Major neurological or medical illness including seizure disorder or syncope;

          5. Metallic implants;

          6. History of rTMS treatment;

          7. Pregnancy.
